WEBVTT

00:00:41.438 --> 00:00:44.066
NO TAIL TO TELL

00:00:52.574 --> 00:00:54.409
This isn't happening, Si-yeol.

00:00:54.493 --> 00:00:57.329
I know. I saw it all,
and you're not going to die.

00:00:57.412 --> 00:01:02.668
So stop making me worry
and please wake up, okay?

00:01:03.502 --> 00:01:04.753
Patient's BP is dropping.

00:01:07.089 --> 00:01:09.341
No, Si-yeol.

00:01:10.592 --> 00:01:12.344
Please, save him.

00:01:12.427 --> 00:01:14.930
I'll do anything, so please.

00:01:15.013 --> 00:01:16.640
Please.

00:01:16.723 --> 00:01:18.975
I don't know what to do.

00:01:20.018 --> 00:01:21.269
Si-yeol.

00:01:21.937 --> 00:01:23.063
No…

00:01:23.730 --> 00:01:25.565
Please, no.

00:01:26.108 --> 00:01:27.442
You can't come in.

00:01:52.718 --> 00:01:56.430
EPISODE 12
LOVE WITHOUT REGRET

00:01:56.513 --> 00:01:59.099
{\an8}WOOSONG HOSPITAL

00:02:06.732 --> 00:02:08.316
{\an8}What is this?

00:02:09.860 --> 00:02:10.986
{\an8}It's a fox bead.

00:02:11.903 --> 00:02:12.863
{\an8}Pardon?

00:02:12.946 --> 00:02:16.116
{\an8}You said the male shaman is after this.

00:02:17.868 --> 00:02:21.830
{\an8}It could be taken from me,
so I need you to keep it safe for a while.

00:02:24.416 --> 00:02:27.919
{\an8}But is it really okay for me
to hold on to this?

00:02:29.337 --> 00:02:31.214
{\an8}It shouldn't be dangerous,

00:02:31.923 --> 00:02:33.967
{\an8}as long as you don't open it.

00:02:36.011 --> 00:02:38.513
It might look like
just an ordinary wooden box,

00:02:38.597 --> 00:02:42.058
but an eight-tailed fox used her last bit
of spiritual power to seal it.

00:02:42.809 --> 00:02:44.770
So that pathetic male shaman

00:02:45.645 --> 00:02:49.065
won't be able to find the bead's energy,
let alone the eight-tailed fox herself.

00:02:49.566 --> 00:02:51.443
No, that's not what I mean.

00:02:51.526 --> 00:02:54.070
Is it okay to trust me
with something this important?

00:02:55.572 --> 00:02:56.865
Why not?

00:02:57.657 --> 00:02:59.159
Well, because…

00:03:00.744 --> 00:03:02.037
you know everything.

00:03:06.666 --> 00:03:08.627
You know what kind of person I am,

00:03:09.503 --> 00:03:12.255
what I'm really like deep down.

00:03:13.965 --> 00:03:15.300
Don't flatter yourself.

00:03:15.801 --> 00:03:18.220
You're not that special.

00:03:18.845 --> 00:03:21.181
Do you think it's easy to be a bad guy?

00:03:21.723 --> 00:03:25.811
I don't believe
humans are particularly good,

00:03:25.894 --> 00:03:30.649
but I don't think
they're purely wicked or selfish either.

00:03:32.150 --> 00:03:34.402
Even if you have an ugly side deep down,

00:03:35.028 --> 00:03:37.322
I'm sure that's not all there is to you.

00:03:40.784 --> 00:03:42.702
Honestly, I don't know.

00:03:42.786 --> 00:03:44.246
At first,

00:03:45.038 --> 00:03:47.624
I didn't think
I was such a bad guy either.

00:03:48.583 --> 00:03:51.127
But at some point,

00:03:51.211 --> 00:03:53.547
- I realized I'd become so--
- You became pathetic.

00:03:54.631 --> 00:03:56.216
That's just how it is.

00:03:56.299 --> 00:04:01.096
If you live life showing your worst side,
you'll only sink lower and lower.

00:04:05.475 --> 00:04:06.685
Don't worry about this.

00:04:07.310 --> 00:04:08.770
I'll keep it safe.

00:04:09.479 --> 00:04:15.485
But is there really a way for me
and Si-yeol to get our lives back?

00:04:16.111 --> 00:04:17.946
Don't worry. Just focus on getting better.

00:04:18.029 --> 00:04:20.323
If you die before I can do anything,

00:04:21.074 --> 00:04:24.035
then there really won't be
any way to fix this.

00:04:25.287 --> 00:04:26.663
What's that?

00:04:27.914 --> 00:04:30.292
Oh, it's nothing.

00:04:31.877 --> 00:04:33.169
Aren't you bored?

00:04:34.838 --> 00:04:36.131
Why don't you watch some TV?

00:04:37.090 --> 00:04:41.011
The gunshot victim was transported
to a nearby university hospital.

00:04:41.094 --> 00:04:43.430
Police have identified Lee,
a man in his thirties,

00:04:43.513 --> 00:04:46.558
as the prime suspect and are in pursuit.

00:04:46.641 --> 00:04:51.187
Lee, who was imprisoned nine years ago
for various crimes,

00:04:51.271 --> 00:04:53.481
is believed to be
the fourth-generation heir to G Group.

00:04:53.565 --> 00:04:56.443
He allegedly committed this act of revenge
immediately after his release,

00:04:56.526 --> 00:04:57.819
shocking the public.

00:05:01.573 --> 00:05:02.699
Kelly.

00:05:06.453 --> 00:05:07.704
Sponge stick.

00:05:08.872 --> 00:05:10.540
- Tie, please.
- Yes, Doctor.

00:05:23.970 --> 00:05:25.263
How did it go?

00:05:26.806 --> 00:05:28.475
We did our best,

00:05:28.558 --> 00:05:31.603
but he was already
bleeding heavily before the surgery,

00:05:31.686 --> 00:05:34.648
and the organ damage was too extensive.

00:05:35.690 --> 00:05:38.818
I think you should prepare for the worst.

00:05:45.575 --> 00:05:49.412
He may not make it through the night.

00:05:53.375 --> 00:05:57.420
Wake up. This isn't funny at all.

00:06:00.799 --> 00:06:02.050
Why did you…

00:06:02.717 --> 00:06:04.552
Because of me…

00:06:06.179 --> 00:06:07.514
Si-yeol.

00:06:08.056 --> 00:06:10.558
I've never been through
something like this before.

00:06:10.642 --> 00:06:12.686
I don't know what to do.

00:06:14.437 --> 00:06:16.481
What am I supposed to do?

00:06:19.025 --> 00:06:20.151
I'd rather…

00:06:22.237 --> 00:06:24.906
I'd rather take the punishment myself.

00:06:24.990 --> 00:06:28.910
That's what you guys really want.

00:06:28.994 --> 00:06:31.579
Si-yeol didn't do anything wrong.

00:06:34.624 --> 00:06:36.543
What do I have to do…

00:06:36.626 --> 00:06:37.919
What can I do…

00:06:46.928 --> 00:06:49.764
There will come a time
when you must choose.

00:06:49.848 --> 00:06:51.933
Whether to become human

00:06:52.767 --> 00:06:56.062
or be forever annihilated.

00:07:06.614 --> 00:07:08.033
Si-yeol.

00:07:09.743 --> 00:07:11.244
What happened?

00:07:24.007 --> 00:07:25.508
Hold on.

00:07:25.592 --> 00:07:26.926
Where exactly are we going?

00:07:27.010 --> 00:07:29.220
I followed you because you told me to,

00:07:29.304 --> 00:07:30.847
- but why are we here--
- It's just…

00:07:31.556 --> 00:07:33.641
This place holds special meaning for me.

00:07:35.268 --> 00:07:37.395
I should at least get to choose the spot

00:07:37.479 --> 00:07:39.064
for my final moment.

00:07:41.691 --> 00:07:43.276
Are you serious right now?

00:07:43.359 --> 00:07:46.321
You said
Si-yeol might not survive the night.

00:07:52.869 --> 00:07:53.995
Okay, look.

00:07:55.121 --> 00:07:58.374
What about that other nine-tailed fox?
I mean, was it the eight-tailed fox?

00:07:58.458 --> 00:08:00.376
Can't she do something to help?

00:08:01.002 --> 00:08:02.003
She can't.

00:08:02.087 --> 00:08:06.007
Saving a dying person
is more than she can handle.

00:08:06.091 --> 00:08:10.678
Then are you telling me
to just stand by and watch Si-yeol die?

00:08:13.181 --> 00:08:15.433
There's only one way.

00:08:17.310 --> 00:08:18.770
But…

00:08:20.230 --> 00:08:22.107
I need your help.

00:08:27.821 --> 00:08:28.905
How?

00:08:39.749 --> 00:08:42.168
This is the Sajin Ritual Blade.

00:08:43.795 --> 00:08:47.632
It holds the sacred power
to sever and defy fate.

00:08:49.592 --> 00:08:52.512
Well, what am I supposed to do with it?

00:08:55.265 --> 00:08:56.516
Stab me with it.

00:08:59.310 --> 00:09:00.186
What?

00:09:01.146 --> 00:09:02.230
I said, stab me.

00:09:03.064 --> 00:09:05.650
Then I will vanish
from this world entirely,

00:09:06.484 --> 00:09:09.445
and everything that was twisted
and distorted because of me

00:09:10.155 --> 00:09:11.823
will go back to the way it was.

00:09:12.532 --> 00:09:13.908
Then Si-yeol…

00:09:17.203 --> 00:09:19.247
won't have to die in vain like this.

00:09:24.419 --> 00:09:26.004
But still…

00:09:28.840 --> 00:09:30.550
We don't have time to hesitate.

00:09:30.633 --> 00:09:33.887
If Si-yeol just dies like this,

00:09:33.970 --> 00:09:36.264
then there's really nothing we can do.

00:09:37.765 --> 00:09:39.684
And that means you'll die as well.

00:09:58.369 --> 00:10:01.331
This is the end for me. My final moment.

00:10:03.166 --> 00:10:07.212
I never once imagined an ending like this.

00:10:28.274 --> 00:10:30.026
But Geum-ho,

00:10:30.109 --> 00:10:32.320
I think I finally understand
your final words.

00:10:32.403 --> 00:10:34.322
The ones I spent a lifetime
trying to grasp

00:10:34.405 --> 00:10:36.574
and could never make sense of

00:10:37.659 --> 00:10:39.661
until this moment.

00:10:41.746 --> 00:10:45.375
My end isn't what I wanted it to be,

00:10:46.584 --> 00:10:49.837
and my last moment may be tragic.

00:10:54.050 --> 00:10:55.885
But even so…

00:10:58.304 --> 00:11:01.724
I lived my own life, just like you did.

00:11:07.146 --> 00:11:08.439
With no regrets.

00:12:36.444 --> 00:12:38.946
So this is how it ends after all.

00:12:48.039 --> 00:12:49.082
Eun-ho.

00:13:00.760 --> 00:13:02.929
Eun-ho!

00:13:05.515 --> 00:13:08.393
Did I really do this…

00:13:09.102 --> 00:13:10.395
It's not like that.

00:13:11.687 --> 00:13:12.980
I chose this.

00:13:14.774 --> 00:13:16.109
Just hold on.

00:13:16.192 --> 00:13:17.944
I'll go get help--

00:13:18.027 --> 00:13:19.570
Don't go.

00:13:19.654 --> 00:13:21.948
Stay with me.

00:13:24.784 --> 00:13:27.161
I don't have much time left.

00:13:29.247 --> 00:13:31.791
Why did you do this?

00:13:33.209 --> 00:13:36.003
You said you'd choose
the solution for both of us.

00:13:37.713 --> 00:13:39.173
But this isn't it.

00:13:42.385 --> 00:13:44.220
Once I'm gone,

00:13:45.346 --> 00:13:47.640
I can't really imagine

00:13:48.349 --> 00:13:50.601
what that world will look like.

00:13:53.020 --> 00:13:55.273
But at least I can save you

00:13:56.357 --> 00:13:59.569
and give you your life back.

00:14:02.029 --> 00:14:04.198
None of that matters to me anymore.

00:14:05.616 --> 00:14:07.368
I just want to be with you

00:14:08.035 --> 00:14:09.620
and live a normal life.

00:14:10.997 --> 00:14:12.498
Even if I have nothing,

00:14:13.082 --> 00:14:16.127
I just want us to be together, okay?

00:14:17.170 --> 00:14:18.921
So please don't die.

00:14:19.589 --> 00:14:21.048
Don't leave me like this.

00:14:26.596 --> 00:14:29.849
Si-yeol, do you remember

00:14:31.184 --> 00:14:32.852
the bet we made?

00:14:34.270 --> 00:14:37.398
You said you'd grant me a wish.

00:14:38.232 --> 00:14:41.152
Yeah. I remember.

00:14:42.236 --> 00:14:44.363
Once everything went back to normal,

00:14:45.531 --> 00:14:48.367
I was going to erase your memory.

00:14:50.161 --> 00:14:52.580
So you wouldn't be in pain

00:14:54.207 --> 00:14:56.042
or miss me.

00:14:57.460 --> 00:15:00.838
So you could live a normal, happy life,

00:15:02.089 --> 00:15:05.092
just like before.

00:15:06.886 --> 00:15:09.430
But I don't have that power anymore.

00:15:10.932 --> 00:15:13.726
Eun-ho… please don't.

00:15:13.809 --> 00:15:14.894
Eun-ho.

00:15:14.977 --> 00:15:17.522
So please forget me.

00:15:19.190 --> 00:15:20.900
That's my wish.

00:15:27.114 --> 00:15:29.450
Eun-ho, no!

00:15:29.534 --> 00:15:32.161
No… Eun-ho!

00:15:33.120 --> 00:15:34.372
Eun-ho…

00:15:41.462 --> 00:15:44.173
I really wasn't going to say this.

00:15:45.341 --> 00:15:47.343
I know I shouldn't…

00:15:49.720 --> 00:15:51.973
so forget what I'm about to say too.

00:15:54.141 --> 00:15:55.685
I love you, Si-yeol.

00:16:17.081 --> 00:16:18.416
Eun-ho…

00:16:19.542 --> 00:16:20.960
Eun-ho!

00:16:29.385 --> 00:16:31.429
Eun-ho!

00:16:35.349 --> 00:16:37.768
RIVER OF THREE CROSSINGS

00:16:58.456 --> 00:17:01.292
As you can see,
the boat isn't running today.

00:17:02.585 --> 00:17:05.504
I don't know whose temper is so damn foul,

00:17:05.588 --> 00:17:06.922
but I've never seen

00:17:07.006 --> 00:17:09.884
the River of Three Crossings
rage like this.

00:17:19.226 --> 00:17:22.188
The test results aren't good.

00:17:22.271 --> 00:17:23.230
At this rate,

00:17:23.939 --> 00:17:26.734
I don't think you'll make it
through the year.

00:17:26.817 --> 00:17:29.737
I think it would be best
to prepare yourself.

00:17:32.114 --> 00:17:33.407
I understand.

00:17:34.950 --> 00:17:36.160
What is it?

00:17:38.287 --> 00:17:39.246
Well…

00:17:39.914 --> 00:17:42.500
I think Mr. Kang's chart got mixed up.

00:17:43.209 --> 00:17:44.293
What?

00:17:46.462 --> 00:17:48.089
Wait, how did this…

00:17:52.385 --> 00:17:54.804
The scan is clean.
There's nothing wrong with you.

00:17:54.887 --> 00:17:56.972
You must have been terrified.

00:17:57.056 --> 00:17:58.057
I am so sorry.

00:17:58.140 --> 00:18:01.060
This never happens. I don't know how…

00:18:01.143 --> 00:18:02.645
I really am sorry.

00:19:00.244 --> 00:19:04.123
What good does carrying
all that weight do?

00:19:04.206 --> 00:19:07.418
It's heavy enough
to sink a ship, you fool.

00:19:08.127 --> 00:19:10.504
Who are you trying to drag down with you?

00:19:14.091 --> 00:19:16.761
Drink up and forget all about it.

00:19:18.095 --> 00:19:20.264
Why are you so attached to this life?

00:19:41.744 --> 00:19:44.121
{\an8}That day, one life ended…

00:19:44.205 --> 00:19:45.414
{\an8}ONE YEAR LATER

00:19:45.498 --> 00:19:47.249
{\an8}…and several seasons passed.

00:19:48.501 --> 00:19:51.378
Kang Si-yeol, currently playing
in the English second division,

00:19:51.462 --> 00:19:57.134
scored a dramatic winning goal,
leading Thames FC to automatic promotion.

00:19:57.218 --> 00:20:00.137
Turning down transfer offers
from the world's top clubs,

00:20:00.221 --> 00:20:06.018
he stayed with his relegated team
and showed true dedication as captain.

00:20:06.101 --> 00:20:07.478
Just as he promised,

00:20:07.561 --> 00:20:11.148
he secured the team's early promotion
in just one season,

00:20:11.232 --> 00:20:13.400
making a glorious return
to the Premier League.

00:20:13.484 --> 00:20:17.279
{\an8}I think this match
showed everyone who we are.

00:20:17.947 --> 00:20:19.698
We had tougher moments, but…

00:20:21.283 --> 00:20:23.160
In that place where life ended,

00:20:23.244 --> 00:20:26.914
everything that was twisted and distorted
returned back to normal.

00:20:27.498 --> 00:20:30.251
The human world just went on
as if nothing had happened.

00:20:37.800 --> 00:20:40.636
Some regained what they had lost.

00:20:44.807 --> 00:20:47.142
They grew older
yet remained free of illness.

00:20:55.776 --> 00:20:58.070
Some never died…

00:21:00.948 --> 00:21:02.950
- and some never grieved.
- Dad!

00:21:03.033 --> 00:21:04.118
Honey!

00:21:04.201 --> 00:21:05.953
Did you miss me?

00:21:06.036 --> 00:21:07.746
- Wait, Dad. That's not important.
- What?

00:21:07.830 --> 00:21:09.957
Do you know who I just saw at the airport?

00:21:10.040 --> 00:21:12.668
Kang Si-yeol! I got his autograph!

00:21:12.751 --> 00:21:15.254
Kang Si-yeol? What?

00:21:15.337 --> 00:21:17.339
Did you get it made out to me?

00:21:17.923 --> 00:21:19.675
Hey, you don't even like soccer.

00:21:19.758 --> 00:21:22.636
I may not like soccer,
but I like Kang Si-yeol.

00:21:25.681 --> 00:21:27.182
TO HYE-RIM, I HOPE YOU'RE HAPPY

00:21:27.266 --> 00:21:31.312
But come to think of it,
I don't think I told him my name.

00:21:31.395 --> 00:21:34.815
You've got your name plastered
right on your suitcase.

00:21:34.899 --> 00:21:38.819
How else would Kang Si-yeol know
my daughter's name?

00:21:38.903 --> 00:21:39.820
- Seriously.
- However,

00:21:39.904 --> 00:21:42.615
even if it seemed
as if nothing had happened,

00:21:43.282 --> 00:21:45.701
it doesn't mean it wasn't real.

00:21:45.784 --> 00:21:48.495
You know that student from the airport?

00:21:49.204 --> 00:21:50.205
What?

00:21:50.289 --> 00:21:52.291
You just seemed really happy to see her.

00:21:52.374 --> 00:21:55.878
Right, you wouldn't remember.

00:21:56.837 --> 00:21:57.838
What?

00:21:57.922 --> 00:21:59.381
Do I know her too?

00:22:01.133 --> 00:22:02.217
No.

00:22:03.761 --> 00:22:05.971
Anyway, you've been weird lately.

00:22:06.055 --> 00:22:10.017
You rarely smile,
and you don't seem to care about anything.

00:22:10.601 --> 00:22:14.855
You don't even seem that happy
about finishing this season so well.

00:23:22.840 --> 00:23:26.885
Your world is truly chaotic.

00:23:33.100 --> 00:23:36.562
Isn't it time you let it go?

00:24:07.301 --> 00:24:09.720
{\an8}NINE YEARS LATER

00:24:10.637 --> 00:24:11.972
H PUB

00:24:18.395 --> 00:24:20.397
We're closed for the night.

00:24:21.273 --> 00:24:22.649
Hello, Mr. Hyeon.

00:24:23.901 --> 00:24:24.818
It's you, Si-yeol.

00:24:25.652 --> 00:24:26.779
Come in.

00:24:27.863 --> 00:24:29.239
Where's Woo-seok?

00:24:29.323 --> 00:24:30.199
Hey.

00:24:33.827 --> 00:24:36.872
Ordering pizza at this hour? That's new.

00:24:36.955 --> 00:24:39.666
I haven't told anyone this yet,

00:24:40.459 --> 00:24:41.460
but I'm retiring.

00:24:43.378 --> 00:24:46.173
Well, good for you.

00:24:46.256 --> 00:24:49.218
Considering your age,
you should've done it long ago.

00:24:49.718 --> 00:24:51.553
You've milked it long enough.

00:24:51.637 --> 00:24:52.805
Right?

00:24:56.141 --> 00:24:58.102
So what now? Are you going to be a coach?

00:24:58.852 --> 00:25:00.604
I'm done with soccer,

00:25:01.105 --> 00:25:02.773
so I'll take my time figuring that out.

00:25:04.775 --> 00:25:06.735
Anyway, how's this place doing?

00:25:06.819 --> 00:25:08.529
Ever thought about opening
a second branch?

00:25:08.612 --> 00:25:10.405
You? Running a business?

00:25:11.073 --> 00:25:13.033
Making a living is no joke.

00:25:13.617 --> 00:25:15.744
You look pretty happy, considering.

00:25:16.578 --> 00:25:19.373
Well, once I actually started,

00:25:19.456 --> 00:25:22.417
it really suited me.
Cooking's kind of fun too.

00:25:33.387 --> 00:25:35.514
You know, when our fates switched back…

00:25:36.265 --> 00:25:37.808
Has it already been ten years?

00:25:39.226 --> 00:25:40.519
Honestly, I used to think

00:25:41.103 --> 00:25:45.732
that had it not been for the car accident,
I'd have ended up with a life like yours.

00:25:45.816 --> 00:25:50.237
But even when the damn accident
never happened to me,

00:25:50.863 --> 00:25:53.407
I still retired earlier than you.
Isn't that funny?

00:25:55.367 --> 00:25:57.786
You've readjusted so well, though.

00:25:59.997 --> 00:26:04.293
With my dad's retirement fund
and the money I made as a player,

00:26:04.376 --> 00:26:07.671
I put everything into this place.
What choice did I have?

00:26:07.754 --> 00:26:09.173
I worked my ass off.

00:26:09.673 --> 00:26:13.177
But you know, surprisingly,

00:26:13.260 --> 00:26:14.720
I've actually got a knack for it.

00:26:15.846 --> 00:26:16.722
What?

00:26:16.805 --> 00:26:18.515
It's not just pizza.

00:26:18.599 --> 00:26:20.559
Even if I just throw
some veggies together,

00:26:20.642 --> 00:26:21.810
it still tastes amazing.

00:26:22.644 --> 00:26:26.398
I guess I'm better
with my hands than my feet.

00:26:28.192 --> 00:26:29.526
I see.

00:26:30.194 --> 00:26:32.487
Then you should've played basketball,
not soccer.

00:26:32.571 --> 00:26:33.822
Give me a break.

00:26:35.073 --> 00:26:37.075
Just try it before it gets cold.

00:26:51.798 --> 00:26:52.883
How is it?

00:26:55.093 --> 00:26:57.137
Hey, this is actually good.

00:26:57.221 --> 00:26:58.263
Right?

00:27:10.734 --> 00:27:12.527
I haven't been here in a while.

00:27:13.946 --> 00:27:16.156
Now that I think about it,

00:27:16.949 --> 00:27:19.117
I think it was all just lingering regret.

00:27:19.785 --> 00:27:23.580
"If only I hadn't hurt my leg,
then I wouldn't be living like this."

00:27:23.664 --> 00:27:26.625
Thinking like that
just drove me into a deeper hole.

00:27:26.708 --> 00:27:29.294
I kept thinking,
"I'm not meant to be living like this."

00:27:30.128 --> 00:27:35.425
And that kept holding me back,
so I couldn't see anything else.

00:27:44.059 --> 00:27:45.394
What I'm saying is…

00:27:47.562 --> 00:27:49.940
you need to let go too.

00:27:51.441 --> 00:27:53.151
Forget about her.

00:27:53.777 --> 00:27:55.737
You said that was her last wish.

00:27:58.407 --> 00:27:59.866
For me…

00:28:01.702 --> 00:28:03.161
it's so strange

00:28:03.745 --> 00:28:09.376
that the only people left
who remember Eun-ho are you and me.

00:28:11.044 --> 00:28:13.839
But if I really forget Eun-ho,

00:28:14.464 --> 00:28:18.176
there'd hardly be anyone left
who remembers her.

00:28:21.763 --> 00:28:23.598
You said you bought that house, right?

00:28:24.808 --> 00:28:27.811
You know, that building
with my old rooftop apartment.

00:28:28.437 --> 00:28:31.106
I heard that neighborhood's
getting redeveloped.

00:28:31.189 --> 00:28:35.610
No matter how hard you try,
that building's going to be torn down.

00:28:35.694 --> 00:28:37.946
And the whole neighborhood's
going to change.

00:28:38.030 --> 00:28:40.032
No matter what you do,

00:28:40.115 --> 00:28:43.243
some things are just out of your hands.

00:28:43.910 --> 00:28:45.037
I know.

00:28:48.123 --> 00:28:49.583
But Woo-seok,

00:28:49.666 --> 00:28:52.544
I feel like Eun-ho is out there somewhere.

00:28:54.880 --> 00:28:57.674
- Si-yeol--
- I know how crazy this sounds.

00:28:58.300 --> 00:29:01.720
But it feels like someone's watching
over me, protecting me.

00:29:02.346 --> 00:29:05.432
Like they're right by my side.

00:29:06.516 --> 00:29:10.020
They said I was going to die,
but my chart changed out of nowhere.

00:29:10.103 --> 00:29:10.979
You remember, right?

00:29:11.063 --> 00:29:13.607
That shouldn't have been possible.

00:29:14.733 --> 00:29:18.362
And lately, things have been really weird.

00:29:18.445 --> 00:29:22.824
When I got injured last year,
they said I'd need six months to recover.

00:29:22.908 --> 00:29:24.493
I recovered in just two weeks.

00:29:24.576 --> 00:29:26.536
Last month, I definitely left my passport

00:29:26.620 --> 00:29:29.039
- and went to the airport--
- Si-yeol.

00:29:30.749 --> 00:29:33.293
You need to live your life.

00:29:34.002 --> 00:29:36.338
This is no way to live.

00:29:37.964 --> 00:29:39.549
It's too painful for you.

00:29:53.939 --> 00:29:55.273
NO REDEVELOPMENT WITHOUT CONSENT

00:29:56.983 --> 00:29:58.193
CLOSED DUE TO REDEVELOPMENT

00:30:17.796 --> 00:30:19.297
I'm hungry.

00:31:18.356 --> 00:31:19.649
Eun-ho.

00:31:40.837 --> 00:31:42.130
Eun-ho.

00:31:42.214 --> 00:31:43.632
You're there, aren't you?

00:31:44.633 --> 00:31:45.926
You're really there, right?

00:31:51.014 --> 00:31:53.308
I don't know if I've gone crazy or what,

00:31:54.601 --> 00:31:56.311
but I still can't believe it.

00:31:57.521 --> 00:31:59.606
You disappeared right in front of my eyes…

00:32:02.150 --> 00:32:04.819
but it doesn't feel like that was the end.

00:32:06.446 --> 00:32:07.864
Even now,

00:32:09.574 --> 00:32:11.743
I feel like you're watching me
from somewhere.

00:32:33.265 --> 00:32:34.683
Should I check?

00:32:51.324 --> 00:32:53.201
What am I doing?

00:33:39.748 --> 00:33:41.875
Finally. I thought
I was going to lose my mind.

00:33:57.891 --> 00:33:58.892
Eun-ho.

00:33:58.975 --> 00:34:00.852
What do you think you're doing?

00:34:00.935 --> 00:34:02.979
Were you really going to jump?

00:34:04.397 --> 00:34:05.273
How did you…

00:34:05.357 --> 00:34:07.609
I told you to forget everything.

00:34:07.692 --> 00:34:10.654
What good did knowing me ever do you?
Why are you still like this?

00:34:11.321 --> 00:34:13.323
You could've just lived your life.

00:34:15.116 --> 00:34:16.660
I can't leave your side…

00:34:18.745 --> 00:34:21.039
because you keep acting like this.

00:35:16.761 --> 00:35:18.680
Why did you do it?

00:35:19.305 --> 00:35:23.268
Heaven is fickle by nature.

00:35:23.351 --> 00:35:26.521
Sometimes it's terribly cruel,

00:35:27.147 --> 00:35:30.358
but sometimes it's infinitely kind.

00:35:31.067 --> 00:35:32.485
Do you trust her?

00:35:33.695 --> 00:35:38.074
I heard she's a reckless troublemaker.

00:35:41.244 --> 00:35:44.622
I've taught her everything I could.

00:35:45.707 --> 00:35:48.209
She'll find her own way now.

00:35:48.793 --> 00:35:52.464
To take on her burden
and defy Heaven's will

00:35:54.132 --> 00:35:57.427
is to invite a far greater burden
upon yourself.

00:36:01.514 --> 00:36:02.640
Even so…

00:36:04.476 --> 00:36:07.312
the rain has stopped.

00:36:15.278 --> 00:36:17.197
What exactly happened?

00:36:18.031 --> 00:36:19.657
I don't really know either.

00:36:19.741 --> 00:36:22.327
I don't remember much after vanishing.

00:36:23.036 --> 00:36:25.747
It was just raining heavily,

00:36:26.498 --> 00:36:28.792
and a long time went by.

00:36:29.459 --> 00:36:30.710
My heart felt heavy.

00:36:31.669 --> 00:36:34.422
So much so
that I couldn't take a single step.

00:36:36.800 --> 00:36:39.260
Next thing I knew, I was back there.

00:36:39.344 --> 00:36:41.471
Namsan. Where I faded away.

00:36:45.308 --> 00:36:47.727
I don't know what they are thinking,

00:36:48.478 --> 00:36:51.981
but it looks like they sent me back
from the River of Three Crossings.

00:36:54.692 --> 00:36:55.652
Wait a second.

00:36:56.945 --> 00:37:00.406
Then all the strange things
happening around me all this time

00:37:01.407 --> 00:37:04.035
really were your doing.

00:37:05.119 --> 00:37:06.204
What?

00:37:08.122 --> 00:37:11.125
Well, I didn't exactly do all of it.

00:37:11.209 --> 00:37:12.919
Some of it was just in your head.

00:37:13.002 --> 00:37:15.046
Then when did you get back?

00:37:16.381 --> 00:37:17.715
Well…

00:37:18.633 --> 00:37:21.386
Like… a year ago.

00:37:21.469 --> 00:37:23.471
What? A year?

00:37:23.555 --> 00:37:25.682
You've been back for a year
and never showed up?

00:37:25.765 --> 00:37:28.393
You just sat and watched me
be a pathetic mess?

00:37:29.644 --> 00:37:32.063
Well, you weren't that pathetic.

00:37:33.481 --> 00:37:35.984
Winning the last season
unbeaten was really cool.

00:37:36.067 --> 00:37:37.777
And that photoshoot last month
came out so--

00:37:37.861 --> 00:37:40.154
Didn't you see anything else?

00:37:42.365 --> 00:37:44.909
Even when I lifted that trophy…

00:37:46.786 --> 00:37:49.664
didn't you see
that I hated myself for being happy?

00:37:49.747 --> 00:37:51.708
From eating to sleeping,
every single moment,

00:37:51.791 --> 00:37:53.877
didn't you see
that I was barely holding it together?

00:37:55.795 --> 00:37:57.630
Didn't you see that I missed you?

00:37:59.841 --> 00:38:01.634
I felt like you disappeared
from this world

00:38:03.177 --> 00:38:04.929
because of me.

00:38:07.015 --> 00:38:09.183
I felt like it was all my fault.

00:38:09.267 --> 00:38:12.228
Because saving me
is why you ended up like that,

00:38:13.438 --> 00:38:15.899
I tried to live my life
as well as I could.

00:38:19.611 --> 00:38:20.945
Why did you do that?

00:38:22.071 --> 00:38:23.573
Why did you?

00:38:26.743 --> 00:38:27.827
Because I was scared.

00:38:31.372 --> 00:38:33.499
I was scared
that loving you would change me.

00:38:35.126 --> 00:38:36.377
What?

00:38:38.212 --> 00:38:41.049
It's been ten years,
but I remember it like yesterday.

00:38:44.302 --> 00:38:47.555
How I felt the moment you were dying.

00:38:50.391 --> 00:38:52.352
If I could just save you,

00:38:53.269 --> 00:38:56.356
I didn't care what happened to me.

00:38:57.440 --> 00:38:59.817
I was fading away,

00:39:00.443 --> 00:39:02.904
and you became my whole world.

00:39:02.987 --> 00:39:06.199
But that isn't right.

00:39:06.282 --> 00:39:08.326
- Eun-ho--
- I want to live as myself.

00:39:08.409 --> 00:39:09.577
I want to live as myself,

00:39:09.661 --> 00:39:12.080
and even if I die,
I want to die as myself.

00:39:12.163 --> 00:39:14.874
If I stay with you, if I love you again,

00:39:16.376 --> 00:39:18.419
I'm going to lose myself forever.

00:39:18.503 --> 00:39:21.214
Then you shouldn't have cared
if I lived or died.

00:39:21.297 --> 00:39:23.257
When I was sick or hurt,

00:39:23.967 --> 00:39:25.885
you should've just ignored me.

00:39:27.220 --> 00:39:28.680
I'll do that from now on.

00:39:29.430 --> 00:39:34.143
I'm going to erase myself from your memory
and never show myself to you again.

00:39:34.936 --> 00:39:36.229
Even if you get hurt.

00:39:37.313 --> 00:39:40.441
Even if you're sick or dying.

00:39:44.362 --> 00:39:46.322
I'm going to look the other way.

00:39:50.410 --> 00:39:52.620
This really will be the end for us.

00:39:58.751 --> 00:40:01.921
No. You won't do that.

00:40:02.630 --> 00:40:04.257
I know you.

00:40:04.340 --> 00:40:07.051
If you were okay with erasing my memory,

00:40:07.135 --> 00:40:12.265
you would've done it already
because I was in so much pain.

00:40:12.348 --> 00:40:13.975
Not for your sake.

00:40:14.600 --> 00:40:16.519
You would've erased it for mine.

00:40:20.523 --> 00:40:22.025
You promised me once.

00:40:22.108 --> 00:40:24.193
That until the very last moment,

00:40:25.319 --> 00:40:27.447
you'd try to find
the best solution for both of us.

00:40:28.656 --> 00:40:30.158
This is that moment.

00:40:30.700 --> 00:40:32.702
Our very last moment.

00:40:33.369 --> 00:40:34.829
So tell me.

00:40:34.912 --> 00:40:36.956
Is this the best solution you found?

00:40:37.040 --> 00:40:40.334
Erasing my memory and living as strangers?

00:40:40.418 --> 00:40:43.129
Then what am I supposed to do?

00:40:43.212 --> 00:40:46.340
Even if we love each other,
we know how it'll end.

00:40:46.966 --> 00:40:49.594
I have no desire to become human again.
Not even a little.

00:40:49.677 --> 00:40:52.764
And your time is running out day by day.

00:40:52.847 --> 00:40:54.682
In the end, it's goodbye.

00:40:55.308 --> 00:40:56.434
Is that so wrong?

00:40:57.060 --> 00:41:02.231
If it ends in goodbye,
do the moments we share mean nothing?

00:41:04.859 --> 00:41:07.153
You live as yourself,

00:41:07.236 --> 00:41:09.280
and I'll keep living as myself too.

00:41:10.364 --> 00:41:14.118
I'm human,
so I'll get old and eventually die.

00:41:14.202 --> 00:41:16.954
You'll live forever, just as you are now.

00:41:18.581 --> 00:41:20.416
So someday,

00:41:21.667 --> 00:41:23.503
we'll have a painful goodbye…

00:41:25.046 --> 00:41:27.465
but the moments we share

00:41:27.548 --> 00:41:29.842
won't be painful for you
when you're left behind.

00:41:30.468 --> 00:41:32.178
Because I'll make sure of it.

00:41:43.106 --> 00:41:44.440
I told you, didn't I?

00:41:45.399 --> 00:41:47.276
I give my all to whatever I decide to do.

00:41:49.028 --> 00:41:51.280
I already started ten years ago.

00:41:52.240 --> 00:41:53.616
And it's not over yet.

00:41:55.535 --> 00:41:56.744
So…

00:41:59.455 --> 00:42:00.957
don't run away.

00:42:41.414 --> 00:42:43.082
Did I overdo it?

00:42:50.506 --> 00:42:52.383
This isn't it either.

00:43:09.650 --> 00:43:11.694
Why don't I have anything to wear?

00:43:11.777 --> 00:43:15.698
I don't know what to wear
on our first date in ten years.

00:43:20.494 --> 00:43:21.662
Eun-ho.

00:43:24.624 --> 00:43:25.750
Have you been waiting long?

00:43:26.542 --> 00:43:28.211
I wanted to get here before you.

00:43:28.294 --> 00:43:29.795
No, I just got here.

00:43:33.382 --> 00:43:34.717
Here.

00:43:34.800 --> 00:43:39.055
I realized I've never actually
given you flowers before.

00:43:41.515 --> 00:43:42.475
Whoa.

00:43:48.564 --> 00:43:49.815
Oh man.

00:43:50.316 --> 00:43:52.944
How did a reporter find us already?

00:43:53.569 --> 00:43:55.529
Eun-ho, let's go somewhere quieter--

00:43:55.613 --> 00:43:58.991
Oh, he's not a reporter.
He's a photographer I hired.

00:44:00.910 --> 00:44:01.911
What?

00:44:01.994 --> 00:44:04.163
We only ever took one photo together.

00:44:04.247 --> 00:44:06.624
Even that vanished
when your fate switched back.

00:44:07.208 --> 00:44:08.793
That's always bothered me.

00:44:10.253 --> 00:44:11.963
But what's that got to do with…

00:44:13.130 --> 00:44:15.508
A long time from now,

00:44:16.259 --> 00:44:18.719
I'll need at least one more thing
to remember you by.

00:44:24.058 --> 00:44:28.771
Besides, I heard kids these days
take a lot of date photos.

00:44:28.854 --> 00:44:30.815
We just need to go on our date,

00:44:31.649 --> 00:44:34.151
and they'll capture our memories for us.

00:44:35.987 --> 00:44:39.782
But how can we have a date?
It's too awkward.

00:44:39.865 --> 00:44:41.158
Don't worry about it.

00:44:42.368 --> 00:44:45.371
I put a spell on them,
so they won't remember a thing.

00:44:45.454 --> 00:44:46.789
So we

00:44:47.415 --> 00:44:49.333
can even kiss if we want.

00:44:51.961 --> 00:44:53.004
What?

00:44:53.087 --> 00:44:55.423
Oh, right. We should at least
say hi to the photographer.

00:44:55.506 --> 00:44:57.049
You guys have met, right?

00:44:57.133 --> 00:44:58.342
Hey, you. Photographer!

00:44:59.510 --> 00:45:01.887
Hi, Si-yeol! Long time no see.

00:45:01.971 --> 00:45:04.181
Mr. Oh! How did you--

00:45:04.265 --> 00:45:05.641
I just loved

00:45:05.725 --> 00:45:07.601
how that photoshoot
you did last month came out.

00:45:07.685 --> 00:45:10.229
So I specifically hired him
for our couple shoot.

00:45:11.063 --> 00:45:12.648
Wait…

00:45:12.732 --> 00:45:15.693
Mr. Oh is shooting our date photos?

00:45:15.776 --> 00:45:17.528
But he's the top photographer
in his field.

00:45:20.406 --> 00:45:21.657
What's this for?

00:45:21.741 --> 00:45:24.618
I called a filming crew too.

00:45:25.286 --> 00:45:27.747
Photos are nice,
but video captures the vibe differently.

00:45:28.414 --> 00:45:30.374
From now on, every moment of our dates

00:45:30.458 --> 00:45:32.626
will be recorded
by the best staff in the industry.

00:45:32.710 --> 00:45:35.629
Jeez, is all this really necessary?

00:45:35.713 --> 00:45:38.257
Say hi to the director too.
You'll be seeing him a lot.

00:45:39.592 --> 00:45:41.177
- Director!
- Yes!

00:45:41.677 --> 00:45:44.263
Hello there, Mr. Kang!

00:45:44.347 --> 00:45:45.931
Hello.

00:45:46.015 --> 00:45:48.976
He went to Cannes and won an Oscar too.

00:45:49.685 --> 00:45:51.520
I thought he'd be good
at filming our dates,

00:45:51.604 --> 00:45:52.897
so I booked him specifically.

00:45:52.980 --> 00:45:55.232
Since we can't really see your face,

00:45:55.316 --> 00:45:57.109
why don't you take off the mask?

00:45:57.193 --> 00:45:59.653
Right. Of course, Director.

00:45:59.737 --> 00:46:01.030
Cameras are rolling.

00:46:01.113 --> 00:46:03.032
See? He knows his stuff.

00:46:03.699 --> 00:46:04.700
Let's go.

00:46:13.125 --> 00:46:14.168
Eun-ho.

00:46:26.639 --> 00:46:28.974
Mm! This is good.

00:46:50.287 --> 00:46:52.123
Hold on. Wait.

00:46:52.915 --> 00:46:56.085
The background is great here.
Could you two stand right there?

00:46:56.168 --> 00:46:58.921
Really? You think it's a good photo spot?

00:46:59.004 --> 00:47:00.631
Great!

00:47:00.714 --> 00:47:02.842
Si-yeol, big smile!

00:47:03.843 --> 00:47:05.428
Make it look natural!

00:47:08.097 --> 00:47:10.349
Could you give me a different pose?

00:47:10.850 --> 00:47:11.892
A different pose?

00:47:13.310 --> 00:47:14.645
Maybe try a kiss or something.

00:47:15.354 --> 00:47:17.565
But there are too many people here.

00:47:18.232 --> 00:47:19.859
No one will remember.

00:47:19.942 --> 00:47:22.069
I'll make sure
there isn't any press coverage.

00:47:23.237 --> 00:47:24.238
Here.

00:47:31.203 --> 00:47:33.330
Okay, that was great.

00:47:42.798 --> 00:47:44.967
Today was so much fun, wasn't it?

00:47:45.759 --> 00:47:46.677
Yeah.

00:47:47.887 --> 00:47:51.098
Hold on, let me fix your hair.

00:47:51.182 --> 00:47:52.433
Okay.

00:47:55.311 --> 00:47:57.146
What should we do now?

00:47:57.229 --> 00:47:58.814
Well…

00:48:00.149 --> 00:48:01.400
I was thinking

00:48:02.318 --> 00:48:04.987
maybe we should go somewhere
without all these people.

00:48:07.406 --> 00:48:08.824
What?

00:48:09.366 --> 00:48:12.495
We've got plenty of photos and videos,
so I just want to be alone with you.

00:48:13.162 --> 00:48:14.914
Just the two of us?

00:48:19.043 --> 00:48:20.336
In that case,

00:48:22.379 --> 00:48:24.215
do you want to go to my place?

00:48:25.799 --> 00:48:27.051
What?

00:48:42.608 --> 00:48:43.692
Come on in.

00:48:47.154 --> 00:48:51.116
Wow. So this really is North Korea.

00:48:51.742 --> 00:48:53.452
I didn't know that last time I was here.

00:48:54.703 --> 00:48:56.664
Well, it is Myohyangsan Mountain.

00:48:59.333 --> 00:49:01.627
Man, I haven't been here in ages.

00:49:02.253 --> 00:49:03.921
I came here once, ten years ago.

00:49:11.345 --> 00:49:15.057
So you lived in this huge place
all by yourself?

00:49:15.724 --> 00:49:16.767
All that time?

00:49:21.355 --> 00:49:22.439
Yeah.

00:49:23.065 --> 00:49:23.983
I suppose.

00:49:34.243 --> 00:49:35.286
What's this?

00:49:36.829 --> 00:49:37.913
It's just

00:49:38.664 --> 00:49:40.416
that I figured you must've been lonely.

00:49:51.302 --> 00:49:52.595
Hey, you're home.

00:49:55.598 --> 00:49:56.473
Hey!

00:49:56.557 --> 00:49:59.518
Why are you in my house
when I wasn't even home?

00:49:59.602 --> 00:50:01.270
Wow, that hurts.

00:50:01.770 --> 00:50:02.896
Long time no see.

00:50:02.980 --> 00:50:05.858
Yeah, long time no see.

00:50:07.735 --> 00:50:12.823
For some reason,
I feel like your whole vibe has changed.

00:50:12.906 --> 00:50:15.409
Right, she became a nine-tailed fox too.

00:50:15.492 --> 00:50:16.452
That day, ten years ago.

00:50:17.620 --> 00:50:19.622
When she sacrificed herself for you,

00:50:19.705 --> 00:50:21.665
my fox bead accumulated
tons of spiritual power.

00:50:22.875 --> 00:50:24.168
I see.

00:50:28.672 --> 00:50:31.133
By the way, no need to thank me.

00:50:31.925 --> 00:50:32.801
Excuse me?

00:50:32.885 --> 00:50:36.138
I'm the one who cured you, Si-yeol.

00:50:36.930 --> 00:50:38.432
Hey!

00:50:40.267 --> 00:50:42.436
What? He deserves to know.

00:50:43.354 --> 00:50:45.731
Ten years ago, she asked me for a favor

00:50:45.814 --> 00:50:49.234
when she said she was hiding
my fox bead because of those creeps.

00:50:50.903 --> 00:50:53.614
If I end up disappearing from this world

00:50:54.156 --> 00:50:58.202
and can no longer protect Si-yeol…

00:50:59.411 --> 00:51:00.287
What?

00:51:01.872 --> 00:51:03.374
If that day comes,

00:51:04.541 --> 00:51:06.001
I need you to step in

00:51:07.169 --> 00:51:09.338
and save Si-yeol for me.

00:51:12.383 --> 00:51:15.761
I'd just become a nine-tailed fox,
so I was low on spiritual power.

00:51:15.844 --> 00:51:18.555
So I had to use every bit
of spiritual power I had

00:51:18.639 --> 00:51:20.933
to save you from dying
of that heart condition.

00:51:21.016 --> 00:51:23.268
I suffered for years because of that.

00:51:24.311 --> 00:51:26.230
Are you seriously not going to go home?

00:51:26.313 --> 00:51:28.399
Stop coming over here already!

00:51:29.483 --> 00:51:32.486
All this time, you've been hugging me,

00:51:32.569 --> 00:51:35.906
sobbing your eyes out,
all because you missed Si-yeol.

00:51:35.989 --> 00:51:38.283
And now you're saying
you don't need me anymore?

00:51:38.826 --> 00:51:39.868
Your house is huge too.

00:51:39.952 --> 00:51:41.286
I swear…

00:51:41.370 --> 00:51:44.081
Will you please shut up?

00:51:44.623 --> 00:51:45.999
Look at her!

00:51:49.586 --> 00:51:50.587
I don't want it.

00:51:57.553 --> 00:52:00.013
Gosh, I barely got rid of her.

00:52:01.515 --> 00:52:05.102
Since she grew another tail,
she's turned into such a sly fox.

00:52:05.185 --> 00:52:07.479
I seriously can't handle her anymore.

00:52:08.147 --> 00:52:09.356
Really?

00:52:09.440 --> 00:52:11.984
I was actually really glad to see her.

00:52:12.651 --> 00:52:14.361
It brought back some old memories.

00:52:14.445 --> 00:52:18.115
You should be careful if you think
she's anything like she was before.

00:52:18.198 --> 00:52:21.702
I think her temper
is even worse than mine.

00:52:22.327 --> 00:52:23.454
No way.

00:52:24.079 --> 00:52:25.497
That's impossible.

00:52:25.581 --> 00:52:26.915
I'm serious.

00:52:27.541 --> 00:52:30.502
It wasn't only you and Woo-seok
whose lives were restored ten years ago.

00:52:31.253 --> 00:52:33.881
Because of me, that male shaman,
Jang Do-cheol or whatever,

00:52:33.964 --> 00:52:37.718
was practically a walking corpse
because of the spiritual backlash.

00:52:37.801 --> 00:52:39.386
But he came back to life as well.

00:52:53.192 --> 00:52:55.944
I guess since he had some spiritual power,

00:52:56.028 --> 00:52:59.239
he seemed to have woken up
remembering what happened.

00:52:59.323 --> 00:53:00.491
So?

00:53:00.574 --> 00:53:04.828
He should've seen it as a second chance
and kept his head down,

00:53:04.912 --> 00:53:07.289
but he went after the fox bead again.

00:53:07.372 --> 00:53:08.874
Reckless fool.

00:53:35.609 --> 00:53:39.279
He went to Seoraksan Mountain,
looking for an easy eight-tailed fox,

00:53:40.280 --> 00:53:42.950
but he ran into a pissed-off
nine-tailed fox instead.

00:53:44.076 --> 00:53:47.996
So he met the same wretched end
as in his previous life.

00:53:49.373 --> 00:53:50.999
I see.

00:53:51.834 --> 00:53:52.876
Oh, right.

00:53:53.669 --> 00:53:57.714
Then what happened to Lee Yoon,
the guy who shot me?

00:53:58.590 --> 00:54:01.093
I saw on the news that he's in prison.

00:54:01.176 --> 00:54:03.262
Did she do that too?

00:54:03.846 --> 00:54:06.515
- No, Geum-ho didn't do that.
- Hey, get off me!

00:54:06.598 --> 00:54:08.267
He brought it on himself.

00:54:08.350 --> 00:54:10.352
We know exactly who you are.
That's why we're here.

00:54:10.435 --> 00:54:11.979
Let's go quietly.

00:54:12.646 --> 00:54:13.772
Damn it!

00:54:13.856 --> 00:54:16.316
Neither Geum-ho nor I did a single thing.

00:54:16.400 --> 00:54:18.944
He managed to land himself
in prison all on his own.

00:54:22.823 --> 00:54:25.033
But… "Geum-ho"?

00:54:25.993 --> 00:54:28.287
Yeah, she grew another tail.

00:54:28.370 --> 00:54:31.623
So I gave her a name since it was awkward
to keep calling her an eight-tailed fox.

00:54:32.624 --> 00:54:35.002
You can call her Geum-ho too.

00:54:37.170 --> 00:54:39.172
Anyway, let's talk about you now.

00:54:39.756 --> 00:54:42.801
Have you thought
about what you'll do after retirement?

00:54:44.636 --> 00:54:45.637
Yeah.

00:54:46.722 --> 00:54:49.099
I've done enough as a player,

00:54:49.641 --> 00:54:52.519
so I'm thinking
of being a club owner for a while.

00:54:52.603 --> 00:54:53.770
For real.

00:54:54.438 --> 00:54:55.314
Club owner?

00:54:56.189 --> 00:54:57.316
Actually,

00:54:58.358 --> 00:55:00.694
I bought a team ten years ago.

00:55:02.988 --> 00:55:03.864
Man.

00:55:04.656 --> 00:55:06.867
Coach, the game's about to start.

00:55:06.950 --> 00:55:08.952
What's this really important announcement?

00:55:09.036 --> 00:55:10.329
What is it?

00:55:10.412 --> 00:55:12.998
Why keep us in suspense
without saying anything?

00:55:13.081 --> 00:55:15.208
Hey, just wait a bit, will you?

00:55:22.674 --> 00:55:24.760
- What the…
- Oh gosh.

00:55:25.636 --> 00:55:26.595
Jeez.

00:55:26.678 --> 00:55:27.679
- Hey!
- Excuse me.

00:55:27.763 --> 00:55:30.515
- Outsiders can't just walk in here--
- Chi-su, wait!

00:55:30.599 --> 00:55:33.268
That's… Kang…

00:55:33.352 --> 00:55:35.062
- Kang…
- What are you saying?

00:55:35.145 --> 00:55:37.105
Whoa!

00:55:37.189 --> 00:55:40.067
Kang… Si-yeol?

00:55:40.609 --> 00:55:45.030
Let's hear it for the player,
Kang Si-yeol, who just acquired our team…

00:55:45.113 --> 00:55:45.989
No, wait.

00:55:46.073 --> 00:55:49.034
Let's hear it
for our club owner, Kang Si-yeol!

00:55:54.039 --> 00:55:55.791
Wait…

00:55:56.333 --> 00:55:59.336
So… Mr. Kang Si-yeol,

00:55:59.419 --> 00:56:01.713
- No way.
- I'm such a huge fan.

00:56:01.797 --> 00:56:04.841
And you're my… role model.

00:56:05.717 --> 00:56:06.843
Is that right?

00:56:06.927 --> 00:56:10.555
I had no idea you thought of me
like that, Seo Beom.

00:56:11.181 --> 00:56:12.391
What?

00:56:12.474 --> 00:56:13.767
Oh my gosh.

00:56:13.850 --> 00:56:15.769
How do you know my name?

00:56:16.937 --> 00:56:17.938
Of course I know it.

00:56:19.231 --> 00:56:20.732
We're on the same team now.

00:56:21.775 --> 00:56:24.736
So, how are they all doing these days?

00:56:25.237 --> 00:56:26.238
Well,

00:56:26.321 --> 00:56:29.241
Beom is still working with the team.

00:56:29.324 --> 00:56:30.909
He's our GM.

00:56:31.785 --> 00:56:33.495
You know how he's sharp with numbers.

00:56:33.996 --> 00:56:36.289
I think he's better at this
than he was as a player.

00:56:38.333 --> 00:56:39.668
And?

00:56:40.293 --> 00:56:43.672
Gyeong-hun finally snagged
the starting keeper spot,

00:56:43.755 --> 00:56:47.426
Jeong-bae retired early
and took over his family's restaurant.

00:56:48.135 --> 00:56:50.887
Yeah, their galbi is pretty good.

00:56:51.513 --> 00:56:56.184
As for Chi-su, he transferred out
and went up to the second division.

00:56:56.268 --> 00:56:58.103
And now he's playing in the K League.

00:56:59.104 --> 00:57:00.522
He even made the national team.

00:57:01.189 --> 00:57:04.693
Well, he was a surprise pick
and only played one game.

00:57:05.527 --> 00:57:06.945
That's impressive.

00:57:10.949 --> 00:57:12.909
It'd be nice to see them sometime,

00:57:12.993 --> 00:57:15.078
though they probably
won't even remember me.

00:57:17.289 --> 00:57:19.958
Let's grab a meal together soon.

00:57:20.959 --> 00:57:21.960
Okay.

00:57:51.031 --> 00:57:52.532
He must've been really tired.

00:58:18.600 --> 00:58:22.395
RIP KANG SI-YEOL
JUNE 10, 1998 - MARCH 20, 2096

00:58:22.479 --> 00:58:23.605
Eun-ho.

00:58:26.525 --> 00:58:27.818
What's wrong?

00:58:29.444 --> 00:58:31.613
No… it's nothing.

00:58:32.447 --> 00:58:35.117
I think I just saw our distant future.

00:58:36.701 --> 00:58:37.994
Is it a bad future?

00:58:39.621 --> 00:58:42.999
Not really, just a little sad.

00:58:46.253 --> 00:58:47.796
Don't worry too much.

00:58:47.879 --> 00:58:50.132
I decided I won't be shaken up
by things like this anymore.

00:58:50.799 --> 00:58:52.676
Like I told you before,

00:58:52.759 --> 00:58:55.053
I saw the future when I first met you.

00:58:55.804 --> 00:58:57.681
At first, I saw your friend succeed,

00:58:57.764 --> 00:59:00.392
then in the same future,
it was you who succeeded.

00:59:02.644 --> 00:59:03.603
Back then,

00:59:04.396 --> 00:59:06.523
I thought maybe I just saw it wrong,

00:59:06.606 --> 00:59:08.733
and I brushed it off as nothing.

00:59:09.693 --> 00:59:12.487
But thinking back
after everything we've been through…

00:59:14.906 --> 00:59:17.409
it was a future that actually happened.

00:59:19.035 --> 00:59:20.912
Because I intervened in your fate

00:59:21.538 --> 00:59:24.583
and briefly switched
your fate with your friend's.

00:59:28.587 --> 00:59:32.090
So from the moment we met 19 years ago,

00:59:33.592 --> 00:59:36.303
it was our fate to end up like this.

00:59:37.971 --> 00:59:39.139
Yeah.

00:59:44.394 --> 00:59:46.771
Then this sad future you just saw

00:59:47.689 --> 00:59:49.858
is going to happen eventually, right?

00:59:50.483 --> 00:59:53.069
And you're really okay with that?

00:59:59.201 --> 01:00:00.535
I'm okay.

01:00:01.203 --> 01:00:03.955
Just because I know
a moment in the future

01:00:04.039 --> 01:00:06.208
and can guess the outcome,

01:00:06.291 --> 01:00:09.628
I've learned that it doesn't mean
I know the process or the meaning.

01:00:10.962 --> 01:00:15.800
So in our love, and in our lives,
no matter what ending comes,

01:00:17.302 --> 01:00:18.845
I'm just going to face it.

01:00:20.680 --> 01:00:25.018
I'll only know
what that ending really means to me

01:00:25.101 --> 01:00:28.647
after I've lived through it all.

01:00:54.172 --> 01:00:55.465
What do you think?

01:00:56.675 --> 01:00:57.592
It's nice.

01:00:57.676 --> 01:01:00.136
Just the two of us on a deserted island.

01:01:00.220 --> 01:01:01.221
It's kind of romantic.

01:01:02.889 --> 01:01:04.057
Right?

01:01:05.475 --> 01:01:07.519
I'm building a two-story house over there,

01:01:07.602 --> 01:01:09.271
but I'm currently revising
the floor plans.

01:01:09.354 --> 01:01:11.481
It was supposed to be a villa just for me,

01:01:11.564 --> 01:01:13.316
but since we're going to live
together now,

01:01:13.400 --> 01:01:15.235
the layout ended up changing a lot.

01:01:15.318 --> 01:01:17.570
Oh, over there?

01:01:18.905 --> 01:01:20.282
Can we go see it now?

01:01:20.365 --> 01:01:21.491
Of course.

01:01:24.202 --> 01:01:25.537
Let's go.

01:01:30.083 --> 01:01:32.377
If there's anything you need,
just let me know.

01:01:32.460 --> 01:01:34.087
I'll make sure to include it.

01:01:34.838 --> 01:01:37.966
Well, from what I heard,
it sounds like we're all set.

01:01:39.509 --> 01:01:40.719
Besides,

01:01:41.803 --> 01:01:43.763
I just need you by my side.

01:01:45.765 --> 01:01:47.183
Stop it.

01:01:49.144 --> 01:01:53.106
By the way, where's the dock going to be?

01:01:53.898 --> 01:01:54.858
What?

01:01:55.442 --> 01:01:56.943
The dock.

01:01:57.027 --> 01:01:58.486
For the boats to come and go.

01:01:59.904 --> 01:02:01.114
Why do we need that?

01:02:02.365 --> 01:02:05.076
You can just hold my hand
to come and go like this.

01:02:05.160 --> 01:02:06.911
It's way faster and easier.

01:02:07.579 --> 01:02:08.955
No, but still…

01:02:10.123 --> 01:02:11.833
What do I do when you're not here?

01:02:11.916 --> 01:02:14.419
Call me. Just burn the business card.

01:02:14.502 --> 01:02:16.755
Oh, about that…

01:02:17.339 --> 01:02:18.673
How should I put it?

01:02:19.382 --> 01:02:21.926
I know it probably won't happen often,

01:02:22.010 --> 01:02:24.179
but what if we get into a fight,

01:02:24.262 --> 01:02:28.433
or what if you get mad at me?
Anything could happen.

01:02:28.516 --> 01:02:31.728
Then am I stuck on the island
until you cool off?

01:02:32.354 --> 01:02:33.355
Of course.

01:02:33.438 --> 01:02:36.399
Did you think dating a nine-tailed fox
was going to be that easy?

01:02:38.360 --> 01:02:39.527
What?

01:02:42.447 --> 01:02:43.490
I'm kidding.

01:02:44.157 --> 01:02:46.534
I'm going to build the dock over there.

01:02:47.410 --> 01:02:49.621
I already ordered a yacht too.

01:02:51.331 --> 01:02:53.333
Oh, I see.

01:02:54.042 --> 01:02:55.126
That's a relief.

01:02:57.087 --> 01:03:00.090
You look genuinely relieved right now.

01:03:01.091 --> 01:03:03.676
No, I don't. Not at all.

01:03:04.427 --> 01:03:05.387
Don't worry.

01:03:05.470 --> 01:03:07.722
Having a boat doesn't mean
I can't keep you here.

01:03:07.806 --> 01:03:09.891
Oh, come on, stop it.

01:03:09.974 --> 01:03:11.684
That actually scares me.

01:03:12.644 --> 01:03:15.105
Then just treat me right,
and you'll be fine.

01:03:18.191 --> 01:03:19.776
This is nice.

01:03:20.568 --> 01:03:23.822
I feel like we've got nothing
but happiness ahead.

01:03:23.905 --> 01:03:24.864
Don't you?

01:03:26.408 --> 01:03:28.993
Yeah. I'll be good to you.

01:03:38.378 --> 01:03:39.462
This is nice.

01:03:55.061 --> 01:03:57.522
{\an8}SPECIAL APPEARANCES BY JUNG DONG-HWAN
WOO HYEON AND HONG SU-HYEON

01:04:21.463 --> 01:04:24.591
NO TAIL TO TELL

01:05:01.294 --> 01:05:03.296
{\an8}Subtitle translation by Susanna Kim